<subSubSection id="5181EA9DFFE3FFA2FF352919FEACFA9E" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1924B916FFE3FFA2FF352919FEBDFBDA" blockId="29.[189,310,1049,1075]" box="[189,310,1049,1075]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading id="426C0E7AFFE3FFA2FF352919FEBDFBDA" bold="true" box="[189,310,1049,1075]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis id="2BEF6504FFE3FFA2FF352919FEBDFBDA" bold="true" box="[189,310,1049,1075]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1924B916FFE3FFA2FF352948FE28FB40" blockId="29.[189,1398,1096,1193]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
A mid-sized cave wētā endemic to the Skippers Range in South Westland. Morphologically indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="DE9BC295FFE3FFA2FE45296BFCD7FB6C" authority="cochleatus" authorityName="cochleatus" box="[461,860,1131,1157]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Pharmacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cochleatus" status="comb. nov." subSpecies="cochleatus">
<emphasis id="2BEF6504FFE3FFA2FE45296BFCD7FB6C" box="[461,860,1131,1157]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pharmacus cochleatus cochleatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="30DCD87FFFE3FFA2FCEC296BFC63FB6F" box="[868,1000,1131,1158]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but geographically separated and genetically distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1924B916FFE3FFA2FF3529D0FEACFA9E" blockId="29.[189,1399,1232,1399]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName id="DE9BC295FFE3FFA2FF3529D0FDC9FB03" authorityName="Hegg &amp; Morgan-Richards &amp; Trewick" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,578,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Pharmacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cochleatus" subSpecies="nauclerus">
<emphasis id="2BEF6504FFE3FFA2FF3529D0FDC9FB03" box="[189,578,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pharmacus cochleatus nauclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="DE9BC295FFE3FFA2FC9F29D0FB82FB03" authority="Hegg &amp; Morgan-Richards &amp; Trewick, 2022" authorityName="Hegg &amp; Morgan-Richards &amp; Trewick" authorityYear="2022" box="[791,1033,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Pharmacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="2BEF6504FFE3FFA2FC9F29D0FB82FB03" box="[791,1033,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Pharmacus cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="30DCD87FFFE3FFA2FB9829D1FBE1FB02" box="[1040,1130,1233,1259]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and with 
<taxonomicName id="DE9BC295FFE3FFA2FB5429D0FEDDFAE4" authorityName="Hegg &amp; Morgan-Richards &amp; Trewick" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Richards" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Notoplectron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brewsterense" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="2BEF6504FFE3FFA2FB5429D0FEDDFAE4" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Notoplectron brewsterense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="30DCD87FFFE3FFA2FED629F3FE6AFAE7" box="[350,481,1267,1294]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It is easily differentiated from the former by its darker coloration and lack of prolateral apical spines on the fore and mid femora and from the latter by its darker colour, longer legs with more numerous spines on the hind tibiae and the presence of dorsal spines on the first hind tarsus segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5181EA9DFFE3FFA2FF35289EFBD1FA0E" box="[189,1114,1438,1511]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1924B916FFE3FFA2FF35289EFECFFA51" blockId="29.[189,324,1438,1464]" box="[189,324,1438,1464]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading id="426C0E7AFFE3FFA2FF35289EFECFFA51" bold="true" box="[189,324,1438,1464]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis id="2BEF6504FFE3FFA2FF35289EFECFFA51" bold="true" box="[189,324,1438,1464]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1924B916FFE3FFA2FF3528CDFBD1FA0E" blockId="29.[189,1114,1485,1511]" box="[189,1114,1485,1511]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
‘ 
<emphasis id="2BEF6504FFE3FFA2FF4F28CDFECBFA0E" box="[199,320,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Nauclērus</emphasis>
’ is Latin for ‘skipper’, after the Skippers Range in South Westland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
